    {"id":"note","type":"text","x":60,"y":760,"width":1400,"height":40,"angle":0,"strokeColor":"#868e96","backgroundColor":"transparent","fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":2,"strokeStyle":"solid","roughness":0,"opacity":100,"groupIds":[],"frameId":null,"roundness":null,"seed":81,"versionNonce":81,"isDeleted":false,"boundElements":[],"updated":1,"link":null,"locked":false,"text":"Audio is used only to DERIVE per-note targets; inference remains exact and conjugate. Intonation and vibrato do not exist on piano —\nthis phase requires voice, strings or winds. Labels are f₀-derived, not clean ground truth, which is why ς² finally matters.","fontSize":13,"fontFamily":3,"textAlign":"left","verticalAlign":"top","containerId":null,"originalText":"Audio is used only to DERIVE per-note targets; inference remains exact and conjugate. Intonation and vibrato do not exist on piano —\nthis phase requires voice, strings or winds. Labels are f₀-derived, not clean ground truth, which is why ς² finally matters.","lineHeight":1.25,"baseline":11}
